# Local state lives under ~/.config/claude-airlock, never in the repo.
*.log

# Vendored dev tools (make bootstrap) — not committed.
.tooling/

# Corporate / internal CA certs are a LOCAL, UNTRACKED drop-in (see README).
#
# This is a safety interlock, not tidiness. This repo is public. A private PKI chain
# belongs to whoever's network it is, and nobody running `git add -A` on a work machine
# should be one keystroke away from publishing their employer's internal CA names to the
# open internet. Ignoring them here makes that mistake impossible rather than merely
# discouraged — which is what lets the same repo be used at work and in public.
#
# Drop .crt files in image/certs/ and rebuild; they are baked into the image and never
# committed. An internal mirror that deliberately WANTS them tracked can still override
# with `git add -f image/certs/*.crt`.
image/certs/*.crt
